5:
This should be all of the harvest that
the Guild wanted, right?
9:
Should be. We finished super early
with your help. Thanks, Selgir.
19:
Isn't today your day off though? You
sure you want to spend it helping us?
27:
Truth is, I'm not sure what to do with
all this free time.
31:
At least with work, I know exactly
what to do and how to do it.
38:
Not trying to be. Just a leftover habit
after being on the frontlines for so
long.
42:
While I might not be the most
qualified to speak on this topic...
Why not pick up a hobby or two?
46:
Yeah, or like... Is there something you
always wanted to do before but
never got the chance to?
57:
How about we stroll around
Palpebra for a bit? After we turn all
this into the Guild, of course. Maybe
we'll find somethingâ€”
69: That was a close one. You okay, kid?
72: Wah... WAAAH! I was so scared!
78:
So your grandpa's a mage? That's
cool.
81:
And you were out searching for
herbs that serve as magic
catalysts...
84:
Yeah... I wanted to help him out, but
then monsters found me...
87:
While your heart was in the right
place, you shouldn't have gone into
the forest alone.
90:
Your grandpa would've been
heartbroken if you were hurt.
Promise me you'll never do it again.
95:
When you're a little older... and
stronger... then you can help your
grandpa as much as you want.
100:
Sam! Thank goodness you're all
right!
102:
Thank you for saving my grandson! I
don't know how I can ever repay you!
104:
Actually... it may not be much, but I
can treat you to a hearty meal at
my restaurant!
113:
Yeah, every dish is spectacular!
What is this subtle flavor I'm tasting?!
118:
I'm beginning to see the picture
now. Being a chef of this caliber is
truly magical.
122:
Sorry if it's none of our business, but
your grandson told us you were a
mage.
125: Ah, I see. Well, the truth is, I am one.
126:
Or at least... in the process of
becoming one!
128:
As embarrassing as it is to admit,
my childhood dream was always to
wield magic...
129:
I never could give up on it, so a few
years ago, I handed the reigns of
this place over to my son and
started studying.
130:
Just last year I was finally accepted
into the academy. I'm a full-fledged
first-year Voluntas student now!
144:
To follow through on a childhood
dream...
152:
Ah, it's just... I remembered
something.
154:
When I was a kid, I used to read this
adventure story. I always wished I
could be the main character in it.
158: Yeah? What kinda story was it?
162:
Oh, nothing special. It was just about
someone who chose to sail freely,
without being bound to any pirate
group or government.
165:
Guess I lost sight of it all once reality
kicked in, and I could barely keep
myself afloat.
170:
But things are different now. I
believe in you.
174: Yeah... I guess things are, huh?
177:
Thanks to you guys, I can now
explore the world as I see fit...
179:
Do things that I forgot I wanted to
do, once upon a time...
182:
This may be exactly what I've been
looking for.
188:
Hey, is it just me, or are there fewer
monsters than usual? Not that I'm
complaining, but...
191:
Perhaps another party already
passed through here earlier.
195:
Oh, hey. I see you guys are exploring
the Kaleidoscope too.
198:
Hello, Alk. Light. It's nice to see you
again.
201: Huh? What're you two doing here?
205:
Just spending some time hanging
out... Exploring. The works.
209: Captain, let's try that route next.
212:
Fine by me! I still have plenty of new
magic that I want to try out!
218:
A lot happened. And now... I think
they're roleplaying?
